  "body": "---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nThe command `truffle create` overwrites existing files with empty boilerplate files without warning.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Run `truffle create contract TestContract`\r\n2. Modify `contracts/TestContract.sol`\r\n3. Run `truffle create contract TestContract` again\r\n4. All changes to `contracts/TestContract.sol` have been reverted without warning\r\n\r\nThis behavior occurs when creating contracts, migrations and tests.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe CLI should produce a warning that the file already exists.\r\n\r\nOptionally, a `-f` flag can be used when a user wishes to overwrite the file.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nAll changes to `contracts/TestContract.sol` have been reverted without warning.\r\n\r\nI'm happy to create a PR if people support changing this",
